#. <section class="sutta" id="mn83"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn83:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 83"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 83"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: Maghadevasutta → makhā­deva­suttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "mn83:0.2"
msgid "Maghadevasutta"
msgstr "About King Makhādeva"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn83:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā mithilāyaṃ viharati maghadevaambavane."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Mithilā in the Makhādeva Mango Grove."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā aññatarasmiṃ padese sitaṃ pātvākāsi."
msgstr "Then the Buddha smiled at a certain spot."

msgctxt "mn83:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato ānandassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda thought:"

msgctxt "mn83:2.3"
msgid "“ko nu kho hetu, ko paccayo bhagavato sitassa pātukammāya?"
msgstr "“What is the cause, what is the reason why the Buddha smiled?"

msgctxt "mn83:2.4"
msgid "Na akāraṇena tathāgatā sitaṃ pātukarontī”ti."
msgstr "Realized Ones do not smile for no reason.”"

msgctxt "mn83:2.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando ekaṃsaṃ cīvaraṃ katvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ "
"paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Ānanda got up from his seat, arranged his robe over one shoulder, "
"raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said:"

msgctxt "mn83:2.6"
msgid "“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo bhagavato sitassa pātukammāya?"
msgstr "“What is the cause, what is the reason why the Buddha smiled?"

msgctxt "mn83:2.7"
msgid "Na akāraṇena tathāgatā sitaṃ pātukarontī”ti."
msgstr "Realized Ones do not smile for no reason.”"

# In such contexts, dhamma approaches the later Hindu use of svadharma, i.e. the duty appropriate for ones’ station. Compare the rukkhadhamma at AN 6.54
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.75"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Bhūtapubbaṃ, ānanda, imissāyeva mithilāyaṃ rājā ahosi maghadevo nāma "
"dhammiko dhammarājā dhamme ṭhito mahārājā;"
msgstr ""
"“Once upon a time, Ānanda, right here in Mithilā there was a just and "
"principled king named Makhādeva, a great king who stood by his duty."

msgctxt "mn83:3.2"
msgid "dhammaṃ carati brāhmaṇagahapatikesu negamesu ceva jānapadesu ca;"
msgstr ""
"He justly treated brahmins and householders, and people of town and country."

msgctxt "mn83:3.3"
msgid "uposathañca upavasati cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ aṭṭhamiñca pakkhassa."
msgstr ""
"And he observed the sabbath on the fourteenth, fifteenth, and eighth of the "
"fortnight."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, ānanda, rājā maghadevo bahūnaṃ vassānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasatānaṃ "
"bahūnaṃ vassasahassānaṃ accayena kappakaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"Then, after many years, many hundred years, many thousand years had passed, "
"King Makhādeva addressed his barber:"

msgctxt "mn83:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘yadā me, samma kappaka, passeyyāsi sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni, atha me "
"āroceyyāsī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘My dear barber, when you see grey hairs growing on my head, please tell me.’"

msgctxt "mn83:4.3"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, ānanda, kappako rañño maghadevassa paccassosi."
msgstr "‘Yes, Your Majesty,’ replied the barber."

msgctxt "mn83:4.4"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho, ānanda, kappako bahūnaṃ vassānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasatānaṃ bahūnaṃ "
"vassasahassānaṃ accayena rañño maghadevassa sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni."
msgstr ""
"When many thousands of years had passed, the barber saw grey hairs growing "
"on the king’s head."

msgctxt "mn83:4.5"
msgid "Disvāna rājānaṃ maghadevaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "He said to the king:"

msgctxt "mn83:4.6"
msgid "‘pātubhūtā kho devassa devadūtā, dissanti sirasmiṃ palitāni jātānī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The messengers of the gods have shown themselves to you. Grey hairs can be "
"seen growing on your head.’"

msgctxt "mn83:4.7"
msgid ""
"‘Tena hi, samma kappaka, tāni palitāni sādhukaṃ saṇḍāsena uddharitvā mama "
"añjalismiṃ patiṭṭhāpehī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Well then, my dear barber, carefully pull them out with tweezers and place "
"them in my cupped hands.’"

msgctxt "mn83:4.8"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, ānanda, kappako rañño maghadevassa paṭissutvā tāni "
"palitāni sādhukaṃ saṇḍāsena uddharitvā rañño maghadevassa añjalismiṃ "
"patiṭṭhāpesi."
msgstr "‘Yes, Your Majesty,’ replied the barber, and he did as the king said."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.76"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:4.9"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, ānanda, rājā maghadevo kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā jeṭṭhaputtaṃ "
"kumāraṃ āmantāpetvā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"The king gave the barber a prize village, then summoned the crown prince and "
"said:"

msgctxt "mn83:4.10"
msgid "‘pātubhūtā kho me, tāta kumāra, devadūtā;"
msgstr "‘Dear prince, the messengers of the gods have shown themselves to me."

msgctxt "mn83:4.11"
msgid "dissanti sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni;"
msgstr "Grey hairs can be seen growing on my head."

msgctxt "mn83:4.12"
msgid "bhuttā kho pana me mānusakā kāmā;"
msgstr "I have enjoyed human pleasures."

msgctxt "mn83:4.13"
msgid "samayo dibbe kāme pariyesituṃ."
msgstr "Now it is time to seek heavenly pleasures."

# BB has “take over the kingship” But cp DN 26, “imaṃ samuddapariyantaṃ pathaviṃ paṭipajja”, which shows rajjam must be the place here, i.e. realm.
msgctxt "mn83:4.14"
msgid "Ehi tvaṃ, tāta kumāra, imaṃ rajjaṃ paṭipajja."
msgstr "Come, dear prince, rule the realm."

msgctxt "mn83:4.15"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ pana kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmi."
msgstr ""
"I shall shave off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from "
"the lay life to homelessness."

msgctxt "mn83:4.16"
msgid ""
"Tena hi, tāta kumāra, yadā tvampi passeyyāsi sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni, atha "
"kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ sādhukaṃ rajje samanusāsitvā "
"kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ "
"pabbajeyyāsi."
msgstr ""
"For dear prince, you too will one day see grey hairs growing on your head. "
"When this happens, after giving a prize village to the barber and carefully "
"instructing the crown prince in kingship, you should shave off your hair and "
"beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness."

msgctxt "mn83:4.17"
msgid ""
"Yena me idaṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ anuppavatteyyāsi, mā kho me tvaṃ "
"antimapuriso ahosi."
msgstr "Keep up this good practice that I have founded. Do not be my final man."

# I am not comfortable with the syntax of this sentence, which appears to lack the expected pronouns. I wonder whether it could mean: “In whatever age of man is current that this good practice is broken, he is their last man.” But purisayuga elsewhere always means “pair of men”.
msgctxt "mn83:4.18"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ kho, tāta kumāra, purisayuge vattamāne evarūpassa kalyāṇassa vattassa "
"samucchedo hoti so tesaṃ antimapuriso hoti."
msgstr ""
"Whatever generation is current when such good practice is broken, he is "
"their final man."

msgctxt "mn83:4.19"
msgid "Taṃ tāhaṃ, tāta kumāra, evaṃ vadāmi—"
msgstr "Therefore I say to you:"

msgctxt "mn83:4.20"
msgid ""
"yena me idaṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ anuppavatteyyāsi, mā kho me tvaṃ "
"antimapuriso ahosī’ti."
msgstr ""
"“Keep up this good practice that I have founded. Do not be my final man.”’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:5.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, ānanda, rājā maghadevo kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā jeṭṭhaputtaṃ "
"kumāraṃ sādhukaṃ rajje samanusāsitvā imasmiṃyeva maghadevaambavane "
"kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbaji."
msgstr ""
"And so, after giving a prize village to the barber and carefully instructing "
"the crown prince in kingship, King Makhādeva shaved off his hair and beard, "
"dressed in ocher robes, and went forth from the lay life to homelessness "
"here in this mango grove."

#. VAR: abyābajjhena → abyāpajjhena (bj, s1-3, km) | avyāpajjhena (pts1) | abyāpajjena (mr)
msgctxt "mn83:5.2"
msgid ""
"So mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihāsi, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā "
"tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya "
"sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena "
"averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihāsi."
msgstr ""
"He meditated spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the "
"second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, "
"across, everywhere, all around, he spread a heart full of love to the whole "
"world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will."

msgctxt "mn83:5.3"
msgid "Karuṇāsahagatena cetasā …"
msgstr "He meditated spreading a heart full of compassion …"

msgctxt "mn83:5.4"
msgid "muditāsahagatena cetasā …"
msgstr "rejoicing …"

msgctxt "mn83:5.5"
msgid ""
"upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihāsi, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā "
"tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya "
"sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena "
"averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihāsi."
msgstr ""
"equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the "
"fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, he "
"spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, "
"limitless, free of enmity and ill will."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:6.1"
msgid ""
"Rājā kho panānanda, maghadevo caturāsītivassasahassāni kumārakīḷitaṃ kīḷi, "
"caturāsītivassasahassāni oparajjaṃ kāresi, caturāsītivassasahassāni rajjaṃ "
"kāresi, caturāsītivassasahassāni imasmiṃyeva maghadevaambavane agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajito brahmacariyamacari."
msgstr ""
"For 84,000 years King Makhādeva played games as a child, for 84,000 years he "
"acted as viceroy, for 84,000 years he ruled the realm, and for 84,000 years "
"he led the spiritual life after going forth here in this mango grove."

msgctxt "mn83:6.2"
msgid ""
"So cattāro brahmavihāre bhāvetvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā brahmalokūpago "
"ahosi."
msgstr ""
"Having developed these four Brahmā meditations, when his body broke up, "
"after death, he was reborn in a good place, a Brahmā realm."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.77"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:7.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rañño, ānanda, maghadevassa putto bahūnaṃ vassānaṃ bahūnaṃ "
"vassasatānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasahassānaṃ accayena kappakaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"Then, after many years, many hundred years, many thousand years had passed, "
"King Makhādeva’s son addressed his barber:"

msgctxt "mn83:7.2"
msgid ""
"‘yadā me, samma kappaka, passeyyāsi sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni, atha kho "
"āroceyyāsī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘My dear barber, when you see grey hairs growing on my head, please tell me.’"

msgctxt "mn83:7.3"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, ānanda, kappako rañño maghadevassa puttassa paccassosi."
msgstr "And all unfolded as in the case of his father."

msgctxt "mn83:7.4"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho, ānanda, kappako bahūnaṃ vassānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasatānaṃ bahūnaṃ "
"vassasahassānaṃ accayena rañño maghadevassa puttassa sirasmiṃ palitāni "
"jātāni."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:7.5"
msgid "Disvāna rañño maghadevassa puttaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:7.6"
msgid "‘pātubhūtā kho devassa devadūtā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:7.7"
msgid "dissanti sirasmiṃ palitāni jātānī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:7.8"
msgid ""
"‘Tena hi, samma kappaka, tāni palitāni sādhukaṃ saṇḍāsena uddharitvā mama "
"añjalismiṃ patiṭṭhāpehī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:7.9"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, ānanda, kappako rañño maghadevassa puttassa paṭissutvā "
"tāni palitāni sādhukaṃ saṇḍāsena uddharitvā rañño maghadevassa puttassa "
"añjalismiṃ patiṭṭhāpesi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:8.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, ānanda, rañño maghadevassa putto kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā "
"jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ āmantāpetvā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:8.2"
msgid "‘pātubhūtā kho me, tāta kumāra, devadūtā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:8.3"
msgid "dissanti sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:8.4"
msgid "bhuttā kho pana me mānusakā kāmā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:8.5"
msgid "samayo dibbe kāme pariyesituṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:8.6"
msgid "Ehi tvaṃ, tāta kumāra, imaṃ rajjaṃ paṭipajja."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:8.7"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ pana kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:8.8"
msgid ""
"Tena hi, tāta kumāra, yadā tvampi passeyyāsi sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni, atha "
"kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ sādhukaṃ rajje samanusāsitvā "
"kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ "
"pabbajeyyāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:8.9"
msgid ""
"Yena me idaṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ anuppavatteyyāsi, mā kho me tvaṃ "
"antimapuriso ahosi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:8.10"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ kho, tāta kumāra, purisayuge vattamāne evarūpassa kalyāṇassa vattassa "
"samucchedo hoti so tesaṃ antimapuriso hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:8.11"
msgid "Taṃ tāhaṃ, tāta kumāra, evaṃ vadāmi—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:8.12"
msgid ""
"yena me idaṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ anuppavatteyyāsi, mā kho me tvaṃ "
"antimapuriso ahosī’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.78"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:9.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, ānanda, rañño maghadevassa putto kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā "
"jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ sādhukaṃ rajje samanusāsitvā imasmiṃyeva "
"maghadevaambavane kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbaji."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:9.2"
msgid ""
"So mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihāsi, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā "
"tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya "
"sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena "
"averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:9.3"
msgid "Karuṇāsahagatena cetasā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:9.4"
msgid "muditāsahagatena cetasā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:9.5"
msgid ""
"upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihāsi, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā "
"tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya "
"sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena "
"averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:9.6"
msgid ""
"Rañño kho panānanda, maghadevassa putto caturāsītivassasahassāni "
"kumārakīḷitaṃ kīḷi, caturāsītivassasahassāni oparajjaṃ kāresi, "
"caturāsītivassasahassāni rajjaṃ kāresi, caturāsītivassasahassāni imasmiṃyeva "
"maghadevaambavane agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito brahmacariyamacari."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:9.7"
msgid ""
"So cattāro brahmavihāre bhāvetvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā brahmalokūpago "
"ahosi."
msgstr ""
"And having developed the four Brahmā meditations, when his body broke up, "
"after death, Makhādeva’s son was reborn in a good place, a Brahmā realm."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:10.1"
msgid ""
"Rañño kho panānanda, maghadevassa puttapaputtakā tassa paramparā "
"caturāsītirājasahassāni imasmiṃyeva maghadevaambavane kesamassuṃ ohāretvā "
"kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"And a lineage of 84,000 kings, sons of sons of King Makhādeva, shaved off "
"their hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth from the lay "
"life to homelessness here in this mango grove."

msgctxt "mn83:10.2"
msgid ""
"Te mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihariṃsu, tathā dutiyaṃ, "
"tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya "
"sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena "
"averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihariṃsu."
msgstr "They meditated spreading a heart full of love …"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:11.1"
msgid "Karuṇāsahagatena cetasā …"
msgstr "compassion …"

msgctxt "mn83:11.2"
msgid "muditāsahagatena cetasā …"
msgstr "rejoicing …"

msgctxt "mn83:11.3"
msgid ""
"upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihariṃsu, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā "
"tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya "
"sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena "
"averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihariṃsu."
msgstr ""
"equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the "
"fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they "
"spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, "
"limitless, free of enmity and ill will."

# For the record, this totals 28,224,000,000 years, which is the same order of magnitude of current estimates of the age of the Universe, at about 14,000,000,000.
msgctxt "mn83:11.4"
msgid ""
"Caturāsītivassasahassāni kumārakīḷitaṃ kīḷiṃsu, caturāsītivassasahassāni "
"oparajjaṃ kāresuṃ, caturāsītivassasahassāni rajjaṃ kāresuṃ, "
"caturāsītivassasahassāni imasmiṃyeva maghadevaambavane agārasmā anagāriyaṃ "
"pabbajitā brahmacariyamacariṃsu."
msgstr ""
"For 84,000 years they played games as a child, for 84,000 years they acted "
"as viceroy, for 84,000 years they ruled the realm, and for 84,000 years they "
"led the spiritual life after going forth here in this mango grove."

msgctxt "mn83:11.5"
msgid ""
"Te cattāro brahmavihāre bhāvetvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā brahmalokūpagā "
"ahesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"And having developed the four Brahmā meditations, when their bodies broke "
"up, after death, they were reborn in a good place, a Brahmā realm."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. VAR: rājā → rājānaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn83:12.1"
msgid ""
"Nimi tesaṃ rājā pacchimako ahosi dhammiko dhammarājā dhamme ṭhito mahārājā;"
msgstr ""
"Nimi was the last of those kings, a just and principled king, a great king "
"who stood by his duty."

msgctxt "mn83:12.2"
msgid "dhammaṃ carati brāhmaṇagahapatikesu negamesu ceva jānapadesu ca;"
msgstr ""
"He justly treated brahmins and householders, and people of town and country."

msgctxt "mn83:12.3"
msgid "uposathañca upavasati cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ aṭṭhamiñca pakkhassa."
msgstr ""
"And he observed the sabbath on the fourteenth, fifteenth, and eighth of the "
"fortnight."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.79"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:13.1"
msgid ""
"Bhūtapubbaṃ, ānanda, devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ sudhammāyaṃ sabhāyaṃ sannisinnānaṃ "
"sannipatitānaṃ ayamantarākathā udapādi:"
msgstr ""
"Once upon a time, Ānanda, while the gods of the Thirty-Three were sitting "
"together in the Hall of Justice, this discussion came up among them:"

msgctxt "mn83:13.2"
msgid "‘lābhā vata, bho, videhānaṃ, suladdhaṃ vata, bho, videhānaṃ, "
msgstr "‘The people of Videha are so fortunate, so very fortunate "

msgctxt "mn83:13.3"
msgid "yesaṃ nimi rājā dhammiko dhammarājā dhamme ṭhito mahārājā;"
msgstr ""
"to have Nimi as their king. He is a just and principled king, a great king "
"who stands by his duty."

msgctxt "mn83:13.4"
msgid "dhammaṃ carati brāhmaṇagahapatikesu negamesu ceva jānapadesu ca;"
msgstr ""
"He justly treats brahmins and householders, and people of town and country."

msgctxt "mn83:13.5"
msgid "uposathañca upavasati cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ aṭṭhamiñca pakkhassā’ti."
msgstr ""
"And he observes the sabbath on the fourteenth, fifteenth, and eighth of the "
"fortnight.’"

msgctxt "mn83:13.6"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, sakko devānamindo deve tāvatiṃse āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then Sakka, lord of gods, addressed the gods of the Thirty-Three:"

msgctxt "mn83:13.7"
msgid "‘iccheyyātha no tumhe, mārisā, nimiṃ rājānaṃ daṭṭhun’ti?"
msgstr "‘Good sirs, would you like to see King Nimi?’"

msgctxt "mn83:13.8"
msgid "‘Icchāma mayaṃ, mārisa, nimiṃ rājānaṃ daṭṭhun’ti."
msgstr "‘We would.’"

#. VAR: sīsaṃnhāto → sasīsaṃ nahāto (bj) | sīsanhāto (s1-3, km) | sīsaṃ nahāto (pts1)
msgctxt "mn83:13.9"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana, ānanda, samayena nimi rājā tadahuposathe pannarase sīsaṃnhāto "
"uposathiko uparipāsādavaragato nisinno hoti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time it was the fifteenth day sabbath, and King Nimi had bathed "
"his head and was sitting upstairs in the stilt longhouse to observe the "
"sabbath."

msgctxt "mn83:13.10"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, ānanda, sakko devānamindo—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ "
"vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—devesu "
"tāvatiṃsesu antarahito nimissa rañño pamukhe pāturahosi."
msgstr ""
"Then, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, Sakka "
"vanished from the Thirty-Three gods and reappeared in front of King Nimi."

msgctxt "mn83:13.11"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, sakko devānamindo nimiṃ rājānaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then he said to the king:"

msgctxt "mn83:13.12"
msgid "‘lābhā te, mahārāja, suladdhaṃ te, mahārāja."
msgstr "‘You’re fortunate, great king, so very fortunate."

# BB omits to translate kittayamanarupa.
msgctxt "mn83:13.13"
msgid ""
"Devā, mahārāja, tāvatiṃsā sudhammāyaṃ sabhāyaṃ kittayamānarūpā sannisinnā:"
msgstr ""
"The gods of the Thirty-Three were sitting together in the Hall of Justice, "
"where they spoke very highly of you."

msgctxt "mn83:13.14"
msgid "“lābhā vata, bho, videhānaṃ, suladdhaṃ vata, bho, videhānaṃ, "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:13.15"
msgid "yesaṃ nimi rājā dhammiko dhammarājā dhamme ṭhito mahārājā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:13.16"
msgid "dhammaṃ carati brāhmaṇagahapatikesu negamesu ceva jānapadesu ca;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:13.17"
msgid "uposathañca upavasati cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ aṭṭhamiñca pakkhassā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:13.18"
msgid "Devā te, mahārāja, tāvatiṃsā dassanakāmā."
msgstr "They would like to see you."

msgctxt "mn83:13.19"
msgid "Tassa te ahaṃ, mahārāja, sahassayuttaṃ ājaññarathaṃ pahiṇissāmi;"
msgstr ""
"I shall send a chariot harnessed with a thousand thoroughbreds for you, "
"great king."

msgctxt "mn83:13.20"
msgid "abhiruheyyāsi, mahārāja, dibbaṃ yānaṃ avikampamāno’ti."
msgstr "Mount the heavenly chariot, great king! Do not waver.’"

msgctxt "mn83:13.21"
msgid "Adhivāsesi kho, ānanda, nimi rājā tuṇhībhāvena."
msgstr "King Nimi consented in silence."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.80"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:13.22"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, ānanda, sakko devānamindo nimissa rañño adhivāsanaṃ viditvā—"
"seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā "
"bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—nimissa rañño pamukhe antarahito devesu "
"tāvatiṃsesu pāturahosi."
msgstr ""
"Then, knowing that the king had accepted, as easily as a strong person would "
"extend or contract their arm, Sakka vanished from King Nimi and reappeared "
"among the Thirty-Three gods."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:14.1"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, sakko devānamindo mātaliṃ saṅgāhakaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then Sakka, lord of gods, addressed his charioteer Mātali:"

msgctxt "mn83:14.2"
msgid ""
"‘ehi tvaṃ, samma mātali, sahassayuttaṃ ājaññarathaṃ yojetvā nimiṃ rājānaṃ "
"upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadehi—"
msgstr ""
"‘Come, dear Mātali, harness the chariot with a thousand thoroughbreds. Then "
"go to King Nimi and say:"

msgctxt "mn83:14.3"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ te, mahārāja, sahassayutto ājaññaratho sakkena devānamindena pesito;"
msgstr "“Great king, this chariot has been sent for you by Sakka, lord of gods."

msgctxt "mn83:14.4"
msgid "abhiruheyyāsi, mahārāja, dibbaṃ yānaṃ avikampamāno’ti."
msgstr "Mount the heavenly chariot, great king! Do not waver.”’"

msgctxt "mn83:14.5"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, bhaddantavā’ti kho, ānanda, mātali saṅgāhako sakkassa devānamindassa "
"paṭissutvā sahassayuttaṃ ājaññarathaṃ yojetvā nimiṃ rājānaṃ upasaṅkamitvā "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"‘Yes, lord,’ replied Mātali. He did as Sakka asked, and said to the king:"

msgctxt "mn83:14.6"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ te, mahārāja, sahassayutto ājaññaratho sakkena devānamindena pesito;"
msgstr "‘Great king, this chariot has been sent for you by Sakka, lord of gods."

msgctxt "mn83:14.7"
msgid "abhiruha, mahārāja, dibbaṃ yānaṃ avikampamāno."
msgstr "Mount the heavenly chariot, great king! Do not waver."

msgctxt "mn83:14.8"
msgid ""
"Api ca, mahārāja, katamena taṃ nemi, yena vā pāpakammā pāpakānaṃ kammānaṃ "
"vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedenti, yena vā kalyāṇakammā kalyāṇakammānaṃ vipākaṃ "
"paṭisaṃvedentī’ti?"
msgstr ""
"But which way should we go—the way of those who experience the result of bad "
"deeds, or the way of those who experience the result of good deeds?’"

msgctxt "mn83:14.9"
msgid "‘Ubhayeneva maṃ, mātali, nehī’ti."
msgstr "‘Take me both ways, Mātali.’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
#. VAR: Sampavesesi → sampāpesi (bj, pts1) | saṃpavesi (s1-3)
msgctxt "mn83:15.1"
msgid ""
"Sampavesesi kho, ānanda, mātali, saṅgāhako nimiṃ rājānaṃ sudhammaṃ sabhaṃ."
msgstr "Mātali brought King Nimi to the Hall of Justice."

msgctxt "mn83:15.2"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho, ānanda, sakko devānamindo nimiṃ rājānaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ."
msgstr "Sakka saw King Nimi coming off in the distance,"

msgctxt "mn83:15.3"
msgid "Disvāna nimiṃ rājānaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

msgctxt "mn83:15.4"
msgid "‘ehi kho, mahārāja."
msgstr "‘Come, great king!"

msgctxt "mn83:15.5"
msgid "Svāgataṃ, mahārāja."
msgstr "Welcome, great king!"

msgctxt "mn83:15.6"
msgid ""
"Devā te dassanakāmā, mahārāja, tāvatiṃsā sudhammāyaṃ sabhāyaṃ "
"kittayamānarūpā sannisinnā:"
msgstr ""
"The gods of the Thirty-Three who wanted to see you were sitting together in "
"the Hall of Justice, where they spoke very highly of you."

msgctxt "mn83:15.7"
msgid "“lābhā vata, bho, videhānaṃ, suladdhaṃ vata, bho, videhānaṃ, "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:15.8"
msgid "yesaṃ nimi rājā dhammiko dhammarājā dhamme ṭhito mahārājā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:15.9"
msgid "dhammaṃ carati brāhmaṇagahapatikesu negamesu ceva jānapadesu ca;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:15.10"
msgid "uposathañca upavasati cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ aṭṭhamiñca pakkhassā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:15.11"
msgid "Devā te, mahārāja, tāvatiṃsā dassanakāmā."
msgstr "The gods of the Thirty-Three would like to see you."

msgctxt "mn83:15.12"
msgid "Abhirama, mahārāja, devesu devānubhāvenā’ti."
msgstr "Enjoy divine glory among the gods!’"

msgctxt "mn83:15.13"
msgid "‘Alaṃ, mārisa, tattheva maṃ mithilaṃ paṭinetu."
msgstr "‘Enough, good sir. Send me back to Mithila right away."

msgctxt "mn83:15.14"
msgid ""
"Tathāhaṃ dhammaṃ carissāmi brāhmaṇagahapatikesu negamesu ceva jānapadesu ca;"
msgstr ""
"That way I shall justly treat brahmins and householders, and people of town "
"and country."

# PTS has the expected upavassisāmi.
msgctxt "mn83:15.15"
msgid "uposathañca upavasāmi cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ aṭṭhamiñca pakkhassā’ti."
msgstr ""
"And I shall observe the sabbath on the fourteenth, fifteenth, and eighth of "
"the fortnight.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.81"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:16.1"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, sakko devānamindo mātaliṃ saṅgāhakaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then Sakka, lord of gods, addressed his charioteer Mātali:"

msgctxt "mn83:16.2"
msgid ""
"‘ehi tvaṃ, samma mātali, sahassayuttaṃ ājaññarathaṃ yojetvā nimiṃ rājānaṃ "
"tattheva mithilaṃ paṭinehī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Come, dear Mātali, harness the chariot with a thousand thoroughbreds and "
"send King Nimi back to Mithila right away.’"

msgctxt "mn83:16.3"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, bhaddantavā’ti kho, ānanda, mātali saṅgāhako sakkassa devānamindassa "
"paṭissutvā sahassayuttaṃ ājaññarathaṃ yojetvā nimiṃ rājānaṃ tattheva "
"mithilaṃ paṭinesi."
msgstr "‘Yes, lord,’ replied Mātali, and did as Sakka asked."

msgctxt "mn83:16.4"
msgid ""
"Tatra sudaṃ, ānanda, nimi rājā dhammaṃ carati brāhmaṇagahapatikesu negamesu "
"ceva jānapadesu ca, uposathañca upavasati cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ aṭṭhamiñca "
"pakkhassāti."
msgstr ""
"And there King Nimi justly treated his people, and observed the sabbath."

msgctxt "mn83:16.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, ānanda, nimi rājā bahūnaṃ vassānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasatānaṃ bahūnaṃ "
"vassasahassānaṃ accayena kappakaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"Then, after many years, many hundred years, many thousand years had passed, "
"King Nimi addressed his barber:"

msgctxt "mn83:16.6"
msgid ""
"‘yadā me, samma kappaka, passeyyāsi sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni, atha me "
"āroceyyāsī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘My dear barber, when you see grey hairs growing on my head, please tell me.’"

msgctxt "mn83:16.7"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, ānanda, kappako nimissa rañño paccassosi."
msgstr "And all unfolded as before."

msgctxt "mn83:16.8"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho, ānanda, kappako bahūnaṃ vassānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasatānaṃ bahūnaṃ "
"vassasahassānaṃ accayena nimissa rañño sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:16.9"
msgid "Disvāna nimiṃ rājānaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:16.10"
msgid "‘pātubhūtā kho devassa devadūtā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:16.11"
msgid "dissanti sirasmiṃ palitāni jātānī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:16.12"
msgid ""
"‘Tena hi, samma kappaka, tāni palitāni sādhukaṃ saṇḍāsena uddharitvā mama "
"añjalismiṃ patiṭṭhāpehī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:16.13"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, ānanda, kappako nimissa rañño paṭissutvā tāni palitāni "
"sādhukaṃ saṇḍāsena uddharitvā nimissa rañño añjalismiṃ patiṭṭhāpesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:16.14"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, ānanda, nimi rājā kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ "
"āmantāpetvā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:16.15"
msgid "‘pātubhūtā kho me, tāta kumāra, devadūtā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:16.16"
msgid "dissanti sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:16.17"
msgid "bhuttā kho pana me mānusakā kāmā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:16.18"
msgid "samayo dibbe kāme pariyesituṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:16.19"
msgid "Ehi tvaṃ, tāta kumāra, imaṃ rajjaṃ paṭipajja."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:16.20"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ pana kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:16.21"
msgid ""
"Tena hi, tāta kumāra, yadā tvampi passeyyāsi sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni, atha "
"kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ sādhukaṃ rajje samanusāsitvā "
"kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ "
"pabbajeyyāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:16.22"
msgid ""
"Yena me idaṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ anuppavatteyyāsi, mā kho me tvaṃ "
"antimapuriso ahosi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:16.23"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ kho, tāta kumāra, purisayuge vattamāne evarūpassa kalyāṇassa vattassa "
"samucchedo hoti so tesaṃ antimapuriso hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:16.24"
msgid "Taṃ tāhaṃ, tāta kumāra, evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:16.25"
msgid ""
"“yena me idaṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ anuppavatteyyāsi, mā kho me tvaṃ "
"antimapuriso ahosī”’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya17-19"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.82"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:17-19.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, ānanda, nimi rājā kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ "
"sādhukaṃ rajje samanusāsitvā imasmiṃyeva maghadevaambavane kesamassuṃ "
"ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbaji."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:17-19.2"
msgid ""
"So mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihāsi, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā "
"tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya "
"sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena "
"averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:17-19.3"
msgid "Karuṇāsahagatena cetasā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:17-19.4"
msgid "muditāsahagatena cetasā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:17-19.5"
msgid ""
"upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihāsi, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā "
"tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya "
"sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena "
"averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:17-19.6"
msgid ""
"Nimi kho panānanda, rājā caturāsītivassasahassāni kumārakīḷitaṃ kīḷi, "
"caturāsītivassasahassāni oparajjaṃ kāresi, caturāsītivassasahassāni rajjaṃ "
"kāresi, caturāsītivassasahassāni imasmiṃyeva maghadevaambavane agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajito brahmacariyamacari."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn83:17-19.7"
msgid ""
"So cattāro brahmavihāre bhāvetvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā brahmalokūpago "
"ahosi."
msgstr ""
"And having developed the four Brahmā meditations, when his body broke up, "
"after death, King Nimi was reborn in a good place, a Brahmā realm."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya20"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:20.1"
msgid "Nimissa kho panānanda, rañño kaḷārajanako nāma putto ahosi."
msgstr "But King Nimi had a son named Kaḷārajanaka."

msgctxt "mn83:20.2"
msgid "Na so agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbaji."
msgstr "He didn’t go forth from the lay life to homelessness."

msgctxt "mn83:20.3"
msgid "So taṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ samucchindi."
msgstr "He broke that good practice."

msgctxt "mn83:20.4"
msgid "So tesaṃ antimapuriso ahosi."
msgstr "He was their final man."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya21"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.83"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:21.1"
msgid "Siyā kho pana te, ānanda, evamassa:"
msgstr "Ānanda, you might think:"

#. VAR: yena taṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitan’ti → yo taṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihinīti (si)
msgctxt "mn83:21.2"
msgid ""
"‘añño nūna tena samayena rājā maghadevo ahosi, yena taṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ "
"nihitan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Surely King Makhādeva, by whom that good practice was founded, must have "
"been someone else at that time?’"

msgctxt "mn83:21.3"
msgid "Na kho panetaṃ, ānanda, evaṃ daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr "But you should not see it like this."

msgctxt "mn83:21.4"
msgid "Ahaṃ tena samayena rājā maghadevo ahosiṃ."
msgstr "I myself was King Makhādeva at that time."

msgctxt "mn83:21.5"
msgid "Ahaṃ taṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihiniṃ, mayā taṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ;"
msgstr "I was the one who founded that good practice,"

msgctxt "mn83:21.6"
msgid "pacchimā janatā anuppavattesi."
msgstr "which was kept up by those who came after."

msgctxt "mn83:21.7"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kho panānanda, kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ na nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na "
"upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati, yāvadeva "
"brahmalokūpapattiyā."
msgstr ""
"But that good practice doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, "
"cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. It only leads as "
"far as rebirth in the Brahmā realm."

msgctxt "mn83:21.8"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho panānanda, etarahi mayā kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ ekantanibbidāya "
"virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"But now I have founded a good practice that does lead to disillusionment, "
"dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment."

msgctxt "mn83:21.9"
msgid ""
"Katamañcānanda, etarahi mayā kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ ekantanibbidāya "
"virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati?"
msgstr "And what is that good practice?"

msgctxt "mn83:21.10"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:"

msgctxt "mn83:21.11"
msgid ""
"sammādiṭṭhi, sammāsaṅkappo, sammāvācā, sammākammanto, sammāājīvo, "
"sammāvāyāmo, sammāsati, sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""
"right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, "
"right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion."

msgctxt "mn83:21.12"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etarahi mayā kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ ekantanibbidāya "
"virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"This is the good practice I have now founded that leads to disillusionment, "
"dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment."

msgctxt "mn83:21.13"
msgid "Taṃ vo ahaṃ, ānanda, evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "Ānanda, I say to you:"

# BB misses the plural here: the Buddha is addressing all the monks.
msgctxt "mn83:21.14"
msgid ""
"‘yena me idaṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ anuppavatteyyātha, mā kho me tumhe "
"antimapurisā ahuvattha’."
msgstr ""
"‘You all should keep up this good practice that I have founded. Do not be my "
"final men.’"

msgctxt "mn83:21.15"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ kho, ānanda, purisayuge vattamāne evarūpassa kalyāṇassa vattassa "
"samucchedo hoti so tesaṃ antimapuriso hoti."
msgstr ""
"Whatever generation is current when such good practice is broken, he is "
"their final man."

msgctxt "mn83:21.16"
msgid "Taṃ vo ahaṃ, ānanda, evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "Ānanda, I say to you:"

msgctxt "mn83:21.17"
msgid ""
"‘yena me idaṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ anuppavatteyyātha, mā kho me tumhe "
"antimapurisā ahuvatthā’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘You all should keep up this good practice that I have founded. Do not be my "
"final men.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn83:21.18"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn83:21.19"
msgid "Attamano āyasmā ānando bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti."
msgstr "Satisfied, Venerable Ānanda was happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn83:21.20"
msgid "Maghadevasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ."
